Description: Bearded head left, within design of concentric circles representing the zodiac. (reverse)
State: Associated with: Roman Empire Ancient Greece and Rome: Roman Empire
Curator's comments: The zodiac on this coin is much earlier than the zodiac designs on other coins of Alexandria. There are also no other known coins for Claudius in Year 8. The authenticity of this coin may therefore be suspect.
Bibliographic references: RPC1 / Roman provincial coinage. Vol.1, From the death of Caesar to the death of Vitellius (44 BC-AD 69) (5173A)
Associated names: Named in inscription & portrayed: Claudius I
